Description: Used Regal guitar. Rare model. Missing neck binding. Has neck heel crack, side crack in treble side of waist, 3 back cracks, back seam separation. Finish has lots of cracquelure, wear spots and scratches. Appears to be rosewood fingerboard. Strap button on endblock installed at non perpendicular angle. Not sure if this is original. Top of headstock shows wear on the tip. D strin tune slightly bent. Bridgepins showing degradation. I will leave any repair/removal to the new owner. This is exactly how I got the item. Top has ladder bracing. String action great for slide playing. Could use a neck reset if conventional playing is intended. Looks like a very short shallow crack below bass side tuner plate. Nut appears to be either wood or discolored plastic. Missing pickguard. May have small crack in the middle of where the pickguard was located in the spruce top. No case. Please refer to pics for condition. This item sold as is, no returns. Thanks for watching!
Title: Used Regal Guitar
